     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "ChebyshevApproximation[func, d] returns a ChebyshevSeries of degree d or \
less that approximates function func. ChebyshevApproximation[func, n -> p] \
returns a ChebyshevSeries of degree d = 2 n + (1 - p)/2 and parity p (p = \
\\[PlusMinus]1 for even and odd, respectively), by evaluating func only on \
the positive side of the domain \\[Subset] [-1, 1]. \
ChebyshevApproximation[func, spec, interveal] restricts the domain of func to \
interval \\[SubsetEqual] [-1, 1].", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, 
    "title" -> "ChebyshevApproximation", "titlemodifier" -> "", 
